    • Method Detail

      • enableDumpFile

        public void enableDumpFile()
        Enables the debugging "dump" file routines. After this method is called the next MED call to loadModel(java.io.File, boolean) will output detailed debugging info to a file in the current user's home directory. The file will be named [MED File Name].dmp.

      • setShowLogMessages

        public void setShowLogMessages​(boolean show)
        This method indicates whether informational, alter, etc., messages encountered during the save or load process should be passed to the Model Editor's Message Window via the Message class addMessage methods. The default is true: show all messages.
        Parameters:
        show - if true, all info/alert/etc. messages will be shown in the message window.

      • earlierThanOrEqualTo

        public boolean earlierThanOrEqualTo​(int major,
                                    int minor,
                                    int bug)
        Returns true if the current MED version info has a plug-in version number less than or equal to the given version.

        This method is intended for use in determining if the current file was saved in an older version that requires some conversion routine to be performed to make it a valid model in the current version.

        Warning: This method returns true if no version information has been read from a file with this MED Utility with the assumption that if no record is written then either the file is corrupt (and it won't get here) or the file pre-dates the use of the record.

        Parameters:
        major - version to compare against the med files saved plug-in version
        minor - version to compare against the med files saved plug-in version
        bug - version to compare against the med files saved plug-in version
        Returns:
        the boolean true if the plug-in version used to save the file is less than or equal to the given version.

      • snapEarlierThanOrEqualTo

        public boolean snapEarlierThanOrEqualTo​(int major,
                                        int minor,
                                        int bug)
        Returns true if the SNAP version used to save the file is less than or equal to the given version.

        This method is intended for use in determining if the current file was saved in an older version that requires some conversion routine to be performed to make it a valid model in the current version.

        Warning: This method returns true if no version information has been read from a file with this MED Utility with the assumption that if no record is written then either the file is corrupt (and it won't get here) or the file pre-dates the use of the record.

        Parameters:
        major - version to compare against the med files saved snap version
        minor - version to compare against the med files saved snap version
        bug - version to compare against the med files saved snap version
        Returns:
        the boolean true if the SNAP version used to save the file is less than or equal to the given version.
